The paper discusses a compression technique for recurrent neural networks (RNNs) that can be applied to small devices with limited compute and storage capabilities. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), or computational linguistics (cs.CL). Given that the paper focuses on RNNs and their compression, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of RNNs in natural language processing and speech recognition tasks also suggests that cs.CL is a possible sub-category. The mention of benchmarks in the paper could indicate that it belongs to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
